<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2003-06/29/content_943546.htm>

Guatemala: Dengue Fever Alert
-----------------------------
The Guatemalan government put the country on alert for dengue fever on Sat
28 Jun 2003 after 2 people died and 171 others were affected by the disease
during the rainy season, according to reports from that country.
The Guatemalan Health Ministry decided to intensify epidemiological
security measures and called on people to take preventive actions, said the
reports. The ministry also asked people to avoid keeping water in
containers such as pots, which could be a breeding place for _Aedes_ spp.
mosquitoes, the vector of the disease.
According to officials, dengue fever has reappeared in the Central American
country and there have been 2 dengue hemorrhagic fever deaths. One person
died in the south and the other at the Caribbean littoral. However, among
the 1782 presumed dengue fever cases, only 171 have been confirmed. Last
year, 1027 cases of dengue fever were reported in the country, with 51
confirmed.
--
